Wash and dry all produce. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%box}. Halve, peel, and
dice the @red onion{1}(peeled and diced). Shuck and cut the @corn on the
cob{1}(cut kernels off the cob). Core, seed, and dice the
@roma tomato{1}(cored, seeded, and diced). Halve the @lime{1}(halved) and cut
one half into wedges. Mince the @jalapeño{1}(minced), removing the ribs and
seeds if you prefer less heat.

Halve, pit, and cube the @avocado{1}(halved, pitted, and cubed). In a
#medium bowl{}, combine the avocado, ¼ of the tomato, ¼ of the onion, and up to
half the jalapeño (to taste). Stir in a squeeze of lime and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add
the remaining onion and jalapeño to the pan. Cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes},
until softened. Add the corn, black beans, @cumin{1%tsp}, and remaining tomato to
the pan. Add a pinch of @?cayenne pepper{1%tsp} (if desired). Cook, tossing, for
~{4-6%minutes}, until softened. Season with salt and pepper.

Place the black bean mixture into a #large bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{}
or #fork{} until nearly smooth. Stir in ¾ of the @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup} and
season with salt and pepper. Place the remaining panko into a #small bowl{}.
Form the black bean mixture into 2-inch patties, pressing each side into the
panko.

Wipe out the same large pan with a #paper towel{}. Heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium heat. Once hot, add the black bean cakes to the pan. Cook
~{2-3%minutes} per side, until golden brown. Season with salt and pepper.

== Finish and Plate ==

In a medium bowl, toss the @arugula{2%oz} with a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%tbsp} and @balsamic vinegar{2%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Serve the smoky black bean cakes on a bed of arugula. Top with the avocado salsa
and a dollop of @sour cream{4%tbsp}. Serve with lime wedges for squeezing and
enjoy!